            <h2><a href="/updates/2021/07/18/receive-api-changelog-in-your-mailbox/">Receive API changelog in your mailbox ðŸ””</a></h2>
            <div class="tag-list">
                <a class="label" data-label-status="inverted">New</a>
            </div>
            <p><img src="/images/updates/email-notif.png" alt="email-notif.png" /></p>

<p>In API documentation, changelogs are important, and your API consumers need to stay up-to-date on recent changes.</p>

<p>Itâ€™s now possible for them to subscribe by email to your API changelog: they will receive a summary of the changelog every week in their mailbox!</p>

<p>Want to see it in action on Bump API documentation? <a href="https://developers.bump.sh/changes">See it live</a></p>

<p>Do not hesitate to invite your API consumers to subscribe to your API updates (available at <code class="highlighter-rouge">http://{your-doc-url}/changes</code>)</p>

<p><em>Never miss an API change again</em> (now, itâ€™s in your mailbox in case you missed it ðŸ˜‰)</p>

